01/11/2002
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov announced Thursday (31 October) that the destruction of Bulgaria's SS-23, Scud and Frog missiles is complete, meeting the deadline to eliminate Soviet-era missiles.
The cabinet made the decision to destroy the arsenal on 29 November 2001.
A month later, Parliament adopted a declaration, recommending the late October deadline.
The US-based CDI served as the lead contractor.
(bTV, BNT, NOVINITE, Seeeurope - 31/10/02)
